What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Packer Bottles Market?

Market Analysis and Size

In nutraceutical and pharmaceutical industries, packer bottles are also known as prescription, pill, and vitamin bottles. These bottles have large mouth apertures, making filling and dispensing tablets, dietary supplements, capsules, vitamins, and other items a breeze. These spherical bottles come in several colors including amber, clear and white which are made of FDA-approved PET and HDPE plastic. The demand for packer bottles has been increased by the increasing demand of everyday packaging applications and a growing preference for cost-efficient and lightweight packaging solutions in industries. Adopting protective and easy packaging solutions is on the upsurge, which are expected to drive packer bottles market worldwide.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the packer bottles market was valued at 5.19 billion in 2021 and is expected to reach USD 8.21 billion by 2029, registering a CAGR of 5.90 % during the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. In addition to the market insights such as market value, growth rate, market segments, geographical coverage, market players, and market scenario the market report curated by the Data Bridge Market Research team includes in-depth expert analysis, import/export analysis, pricing analysis, production consumption analysis, patent analysis and technological advancements.

